## 4. Backend Architecture (example)

### Backend Models

- **Project** — `title, description, techstack[], teamRoles[], commitment, status, ownerId, members: [{ userId, role, joinedAt }]`
  - status: `recruiting | in_progress | completed | archived`
- **JoinRequest** — `projectId, userId, message, status`
  - status: `pending | accepted | declined`
- **KanbanTask** — `projectId, title, assigneeId, status, dueDate`
- **GithubIntegration** — `projectId, repoFullName, repoUrl, connectedBy, accessToken`
- **Message** — reused from existing model

### API Routes

```
// Discovery
GET    /projects                          — discover feed + filters
GET    /projects/:id                      — public showcase

// Auth-only
POST   /projects                          — create project
GET    /projects/:id/workspace            — members only
DELETE /projects/:id/leave                — members only (owner must transfer first)

// Join flow
POST   /projects/:id/join-requests        — send request
PATCH  /projects/:id/join-requests/:reqId — accept/decline (owner only)

// Tasks
GET    /projects/:id/tasks                — members only
POST   /projects/:id/tasks                — members only
PATCH  /projects/:id/tasks/:taskId        — members only
DELETE /projects/:id/tasks/:taskId        — members only

// GitHub
GET    /projects/:id/github               — members only
POST   /projects/:id/github               — link repo (owner only)
DELETE /projects/:id/github               — unlink (owner only)

// Ownership
PATCH  /projects/:id/transfer-ownership   — owner only

// Messages — handled by messageRoutes + Socket.io
GET    /projects/:id/messages
```

